The paper deals with image filtering using convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of neural networks for artistic effects also falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves segmentation of objects in images, which is a topic in graphics (cs.GR). The use of pre-trained models and datasets is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper involves the development of a new method for image filtering, which could fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
